comment: All bite no body, not worth the money.

Very thin. Nose is very Carmel with slight dusty corn with little depth. Sweet on the front and just a slight bit bitter on the swallow. No finish. Falls away quick with not much presence of depth. Not complex. Easy to pick notes. Fair for beginners due to lack of burn and spice

What does dry caramel smell like? That's what comes to mind. Nice color and feel.  

I get a taste that is sweet, but I still get that dry feeling. Almost like honey that has sugared on the shelf. 

The finish is quick and clean.
smooth bourbon with not a lot of flavour.

"0-1: Beyond bad. Complete waste of money according to my tastebuds. 
2: Bad. Simply not my taste
2.5: Sub-par. Ill drink it... but only because its whiskey.
3: Good. Decent stuff, but not a rebuy
3.5: Very good. I might buy again
4: Excellent: Will be purchasing a bottle asap
4.5: Incredible: top of the purchase list
5:Amazing: cost and taste are worth every cent""
